INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (601, 25, 'Day 1: Luang Prabang — Trek', 'easy', 'LUANG PRABANG
Chomphet and Phou Luang Tai (L)

Today we Cycle and trek in Chomphet district across the river from the main Unesco zone of Luang Prabang. We start with a boat downstream to the village Pak Long. From here we cycle to the village of Ban Som (12) and begin an uphill trek to Ban Phou Luang Tai and an extremely remote Hmong Community. It is a 6km trek taking approx. 3 hours.

The community is totally off the grid with no running water, no electricity and just a small primary school.  There are 35 families and  281 people. living a timeless existence perched on the mountainside.

The village is due to be relocated soon as part of the Lao Government''s commitment to providing all Lao citizens with access to clean water, electricity, health care and sanitation. From our conversations with the community, the families are all looking forward to a connected and healthier lifestyle. This traditional, symbiotic existence will soon become harder to see in Laos and Phou Luang Tai is an exquisite example of Community and Nature in harmony. Relocation is slated to begin in 2024.

After lunch in the village, trek back down the mountain, approx 90 minutes. We then ride a looping circuit of about 20 km medium biking on dirt roads with some hills and stream crossings. 

You''ll be well off the beaten path and into a side of Luang Prabang that few foreigners explore.  This village will soon be gone so this is a limited-time experience.

A professional guide accompanies you every step of the way.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());

