INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (651, 27, 'Day 1: Slow Boat On The Mekong — Bike', 'moderate', 'SLOW BOAT ON THE MEKONG (L)
The bikes will be put on board while you prepare yourself for a soft-starting adventure in Northern Laos. Few people have had the opportunity to do this.  The boat meanders down the Mekong giving you plenty of time to get to know your guide, and learn about Laos and the road ahead. A Laos Style Picnic Lunch will be served on Board. Just Relax and enjoy the scenery
Overnight in Pakbeng', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (652, 27, 'Day 2: Pakbeng To Oudomxay — Exploration', 'easy', 'PAKBENG TO OUDOMXAY(B)
After a brief transfer by vehicle, we’ll be cycling in very rural Laos, an area inhabited by hill tribe villagers who eke a meagre existence from the land. Along the way, you will pass villages of Phu Thai, Thai Lu, Hmong, Thai Dam, Lao and Khamu. The people are very friendly and not yet tired of seeing tourists. in the shade weaving on old looms. After climbing a 300-meter pass, a long descent brings you to Oudomxay the capital of the Oudomxay Province. From here we will transfer around the city and cycle along the Kat River to the resort haven of Namkat Yorla Pa Resort 
Distance Cycled: Approx 90 km
Difficulty: Comfortable
Overnight in Oudomxai', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (653, 27, 'Day 3: Oudomxay — Exploration', 'moderate', 'OUDOMXAY- NONG KHIAW (B)
After a 1-hour uphill transfer, you will start cycling at an altitude of 1300 m. Enjoy the great views and the daily life in the Hmong villages dominating this region. A long descent will bring you to Pak Mong, where we will have lunch. From Pak Mong, you cycle over a small road into the karst, the scenic limestone mountains that surround Nong Khiaw. We stay overnight in a resort with fine views over the mountains and the Nam Ou River.
Accommodation; Nam Kat Yorla Pa 
Distance Cycled: 90-120 km
Difficulty Level: Challenging

Overnight in Nong Khiaw', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (654, 27, 'Day 4: Nong Khiaw — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Nong Khiaw-Luang Prabang (B)
Today starts with a beautiful trip down the Nam Ou River before flatter and better roads will enable you to complete the longer distance to Luang Prabang. Only a few minor passes must be climbed before you ride along the banks of the Nam Ou River, with stunning views of colossal mountain ranges. The last stage takes you through teakwood plantations before arriving in Luang Prabang.
Distance Cycled: 80km
Difficulty Level: Comfortable', 'ACTIVE', NOW());

