INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (676, 28, 'Day 1: Luang Prabang — Waterfall', 'moderate', 'LUANG PRABANG - Chomphet Villages and Farmstay  (L,D)
Today, we cycle in the Chomphet district, across the river from the main UNESCO zone of Luang Prabang. From here, we cycle to the village of Pak Lueang, a short distance from Green Jungle Park. We will visit the Waterfall and the flower garden at the park. before cycling on the riverbank through villages that rarely see tourists. 
Cross the river on a local ferry and by bike continue to Kiao Niao Farmstay, a beautiful small resort surrounded by lush paddy fields, we will enjoy the evening with our hosts and learn all about rice farming.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (677, 28, 'Day 2: Luang Prabang — Waterfall', 'challenging', 'LUANG PRABANG - KUANG SI WATERFALLS - LONG LAO MAI (L, D)
We depart early from the farmstay for a short hike to Kuang Si Falls, we arrive before the crowds and have a chance for a bracing early morning swim. 
We start to trek to the top of the falls, and take a trail passing the azure blue Oasis pool through the jungle for 8.5 km to the Hmong and Khmu community of Long Lao Mai.
Ban Long Laos Village offers a unique glimpse of 3 dominant ethnicities living side by side, This Khmu village has grown since the end of the Civil war the government resettled Hmong Mountain people into the same area, it was hard at first for the two vastly different cultures to get to know each other, it took a visit from a wild Tiger in 1981 to fully unite the people. After the trek and Dinner with our Homestay families, we can toast some marshmallows and gaze at the starry sky.
Trek 14km
Overnight in Long Lao Mai', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (678, 28, 'Day 3: Long Lao Mai — Trek', 'challenging', 'LONG LAO MAI - NONG KHOUAY (B,L,D)
Village life starts early with breakfast served at 7 am. Today we have a three-hour jungle trek through the valley to Nong Khouay. You can leave your devices in your backpack as the village is totally ‘Off the Grid’ the small central store is the meeting place and friendly villagers will be keen to meet you and learn about your home over a coffee or cold beer. That evening we can share thoughts and examine the experience and perhaps hear a story from ‘Grandpa’ a wise whitty village elder who loves making new friends.
Trek 9km


Overnight at Nong Khouay', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (679, 28, 'Day 4: Nong Khuay — Bike', 'moderate', 'Nong Khuay - Houay Fai (B,L,D)
Back on the Bikes Today for a thrilling dirt road ride! The brake-screeching descent from Nong Khouay is the perfect wake-up. Then we continue on dirt roads through the farmland and jungle to the community of Houay Fai and another new family to befriend. 
This evening we receive a traditional  ‘Baci’ Ceremony, a village blessing which is given to say farewell to new friends and family.
Cycle 30km (Dirt Road)

Overnight in Houay Fai', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (680, 28, 'Day 5: Houay Fai — Exploration', 'easy', 'Houay Fai-Luang Prabang (B)
Walk out of the Village to the shores of the Nam Khan River for a 2-hour Kayak trip back to the city of Luang Prabang.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());

