INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (726, 30, 'Day 1: Distance — Waterfall', 'moderate', 'Distance: ≈52 km | Ascent: +900 m | Descent: −120 m | End Elevation: ≈1,250 m
Your adventure begins! Depart from the bustling streets of Pakse and embark on a steady, invigorating climb onto the majestic Bolaven Plateau. The air grows progressively cooler and cleaner as you gain elevation.
Along the way, indulge your senses with stops at fragrant local coffee farms where you can witness the bean-to-cup process. Be awestruck by the sheer power and beauty of dramatic waterfalls such as the towering Tad Fane, plunging into a gorge, and the cascading brilliance of Tad Yueng.
Finally, arrive in Paksong, proudly known as the “Coffee Capital of Laos.” Unwind and feel the day''s exertion melt away in the crisp, rejuvenating highland air.
Overnight in Paksong.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (727, 30, 'Day 2: Distance — Waterfall', 'moderate', 'Distance: ≈75 km | Ascent: +450 m | Descent: −1150 m | End Elevation: ≈700 m
Start the day riding east through the undulating plateau before beginning a long, spectacular descent toward Salavan Province. Pedal past vibrant, lush farms and through sleepy rural villages, catching glimpses of traditional Lao life.
Pause for sweeping, breathtaking views of the impressive Tad Suong waterfall and browse the colourful, lively local markets. The day concludes as you roll into the idyllic Tad Lo Village, a true oasis where the sight of gentle elephants and the soothing sound of rushing waterfalls set an instantly tranquil scene.
 Overnight at Tad Lo.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (728, 30, 'Day 3: Distance — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Distance: ≈80  km  (30km Transfer) | Ascent: +800 m | Descent: −920 m | End Elevation: ≈250 m
Enjoy a truly scenic day of riding along gently winding roads framed by dense, emerald forested hills. You''ll pass through the small town of Thateng before following the road as it descends into the enchanting frontier of Xekong Province—a region celebrated as one of the most pristine and least-visited corners of Laos. This leg offers a deep dive into authentic, untouched Southern Laos.
Overnight in Xekong Town.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (729, 30, 'Day 4: Distance — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Distance: ≈70  km  (50km Transfer)| Ascent: +1050 m | Descent: −800 m | End Elevation: ≈400 m
Today, your route takes you deeper into the wild heart of Southern Laos, heading toward the majestic, protected wilderness of Xe Pian National Park. Anticipate a day of gentle, rolling climbs interspersed with long stretches through remote, peaceful villages. Keep a keen eye out—this area is renowned for exciting sightings of diverse forest wildlife.
A section 
Overnight near Xe Dian (inside or close to the National Park).', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (730, 30, 'Day 5: Distance — Temple', 'easy', 'Distance: ≈140 km | Ascent: +1188 m | Descent: −1333 m | End Elevation: ≈130 m
Your final day is a grand finale as you begin your rewarding journey back toward the immense Mekong River. The cultural highlight awaits with a stop in charming Champasak Town. Here, you will explore the awe-inspiring UNESCO World Heritage Site of Wat Phou, an ancient, exquisitely preserved Khmer temple complex offering sweeping, magnificent valley views from its upper terraces.
Our final stretch of road is a smooth, easy ride into the bustling border city of Pakse and a comfortable hotel.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());

