INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (826, 34, 'Day 1: Luang Prabang — Bike', 'moderate', 'Luang Prabang (L, D)
Meet your guide early in the morning and get sized up on one of our quality mountain bikes.  Ride a short distance to the Mekong River, where we''ll board a ferry to cross the river.  On this tour – our newest tour on the opposite side of the Mekong River – you’ll meet villagers, see animals roaming and try local snacks.  
We''ll ride a looping circuit of about 20km (3 hours), medium biking on dirt roads with some hills. There are very few tourists and no traffic.
Look back on Luang Prabang from the river. We then ride on gravel roads, passing rice fields and amazing views. We stop in a village, try local snacks, and observe the village life around us. We continue on single tracks, passing through farmlands and encountering animals. Ensure your camera is charged for all the stunning photos you will take.
We stop again in a village for cold drinks and to watch locals do their business. After exploring on single tracks a little longer, we hit the tarmac a short while to the ferry. We have lunch in a local restaurant near the ferry landing, and your guide is with you every step of the way. 
In the Evening over dinner at a great local vocational restaurant, we will discuss the ride ahead 

Overnight in Luang Prabang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (827, 34, 'Day 2: Kuang Si Waterfalls — Waterfall', 'easy', 'Kuang Si Waterfalls (B, L) Trek and Cycle
Start with a short transfer to the village of Long Lao,  a thriving Hmong community of around 80 families. The community manages an excellent 8km trail that finishes at the top of Kuang Si Falls. we can enjoy lunch and a swim in the crystal waters before cycling back to the city and stopping for an ice cream on the way. 

Elevation: +250 m  / -160 m 
Ride: 27 KM 
Trek: 8 KM

Overnight in Luang Prabang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (828, 34, 'Day 3: Luang Prabang To Kasi — Bike', 'moderate', 'Luang Prabang to Kasi (B, L, D)
A 2-hour transfer by Minivan brings you to Xieng Ngern. In the first part of this stage, you will cycle to Pong Dong Village, jump into the minivan and transfer to the top of the mountain for lunch and photo ops. Back on the bikes to enjoy the long descent into the valley of Kasi. 
First Section  Xieng Ngern - Pong Dong 37 km 
Elevations + 580 m - 320 m
Second Section  Viewpoint - Kasi   46.3 km 
Elevations  + 600 m  - 1,900 m
Overnight in Kasi', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (829, 34, 'Day 4: Kasi — Cave', 'moderate', 'Kasi -Vang Vieng (B, L)
This day will be much easier, as we cover a shorter distance on gently rolling hills to Vang Vieng, which we''ll reach in time for lunch. In the afternoon, you can visit the Tham Xang or Tham Hoi caves, which are set among the dramatic scenery on the banks of the Nam Song River. Relax with a Lao beer and watch the sunset over the mountains you have just crossed.
If we make good time, we can have a dip. 
Ride: 60 KM,  Well-paved roads 
Elevations  + 460 m  - 630 m', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (830, 34, 'Day 5: Vang Vieng — Cave', 'challenging', 'Vang Vieng (B, L)
In the morning, we take a vigorous and steep trek up Big Pha Ngern. This climb is fun and you are rewarded with spectacular views across the Song Valley, the trek is around 2.5-3 hours so we should be back in Vang Vieng by lunch In the afternoon, you can choose to visit the Tham Xang or Tham Hoi caves or perhaps venture a little further to Blue Lagoon 3 for a swim.
(Optional morning Hot Air Balloon ride. $150 per person ) 
Trek, 7 km
Ride, 35 km 
Overnight in Vang Vieng', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (831, 34, 'Day 6: Vang Vieng — Boat', 'moderate', 'Vang Vieng - Nam Ngum Lakeside - Nam Pien Yorla Pa (B, L)
After Breakfast, transfer to the ‘sea of Laos’: the 250 square kilometres of artificial Lake Nam Ngum. A 2-hour boat ride brings us to our hotel to relax poolside. and enjoy the sunset over the Lake.
We will continue cycling on Route 10 on the south side of the national park. to the picturesque resort of NamPien Yorla Pa

Afternoon Ride 
Ride 80km 
Elevation +360 / -420
Overnight in Nam Pien Yorla Pa', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (832, 34, 'Day 7: Nam Ngum To Vientiane — Exploration', 'easy', 'Nam Ngum to Vientiane (B,D)

We can check out later today so we can enjoy the amazing breakfast at the resort 
in the morning, we cycle to Laos Conservation Trust to visit the program there and learn about their mission to protect the endangered species of SE Asia, then you cycle through paddy fields with fine views in the Phou Khao Khouay mountain range before entering the capital city of Laos: Vientiane. 
You’ll ride through the suburbs on your way to the centre of this bustling, historical city situated along the bank of the Mekong. We will stop for a final Photo underneath the famous Patuxai Monument to commemorate the journey.
A Final Sindat meal on the banks of the Mekong to finish the trip with local flavour
Ride: 67 KM 
Elevation +170 / -170
Overnight in Vientiane', 'ACTIVE', NOW());

