INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (926, 38, 'Day 1: Pakse — Temple', 'moderate', 'Pakse - Salavan (B,L) 

Cycle on route 20 north into the lesser-travelled province of Salavan. We will call the  Forest temple at Wat Pa, Salavan is a quiet town with a lot of history as it was bombed heavily during the 2nd Indochina War.

Cycle 70 transfer 35 

https://www.komoot.com/tour/1435539174?ref=wtd&share_token=alK7foXY3luF5AQMAQ4P39jlu7NuNCINNJ4nStksmMspXX3RzA

Overnight in Salavan', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (927, 38, 'Day 2: Salavan To Savannkhet — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Salavan to Savannkhet (B,L,D) 
Head east on the 15 through rural villages and coffee plantations. To meet the main road and transfer north to Savannakhet, arrive in the late afternoon. 
https://www.komoot.com/tour/1435544742?ref=wtd&share_token=af6BOtpC9R1CaDBwTvbE8V1Tw3DOs7PT3yqJ89qjvJiS0Aut8N
Cycle 70km Transfer 175km (4 hours)', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (928, 38, 'Day 3: Savannakhet — Temple', 'easy', 'Savannakhet (B, L, D) 
This is the second largest city in Laos and has a rich colonial heritage. This city is destined to be a big tourist site in years to come. City tour around the old French quarter, making sure to see the street art and visit one of the many colonial style cafes Cycle along the Mekong visit the Bung Va Lake and have lunch at a stilted river restaurant. Visit the Museum and the Temples before a food tour exploring the night market. 

Cycle 45km', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (929, 38, 'Day 4: Savannakhet — Exploration', 'easy', 'Savannakhet - Thakeak  (B,L,D) 

Transfer 110km to the town after lunch we are free to stroll or Cycle the city for the start of the loop', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (930, 38, 'Day 5: The Loop Thakheak — Cave', 'moderate', 'The loop Thakheak - Nakai (B,L,D)

As soon as you leave Thakhek heading east on Route 12 you are in the midst of the karst mountains and jungle. (Karst describes landscapes made of soluble rock such as limestone and is prime territory for caves). It’s a fantastic sight. This portion of the trip is sometimes called “Cave Alley”

With so many possible caves to explore it can be daunting, which to choose from. I’ll give a summary and pictures here of each and you can read more about the individual caves on the separate pages devoted to them.
We will visit Falang swim hole, Elephant Cave and Buddha Cave 

Ride: 65km transfer 30', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (931, 38, 'Day 6: Nakai — Boat', 'moderate', 'Nakai - Na Hin (B,L,D)
The Nakai Plateau is an interesting and unique place. Dead trees and water dominate the landscape here. If you have a spare day, hang out here and do a boat trip on the many waterways. If you’re interested, inquire at your guesthouse and they can arrange this for you. It’s a good quiet place to relax if that’s what you want
.
Dead trees will dominate the start of your drive today as you weave through the Nam Theun 2 Reservoir and a few small villages. There’s a stark beauty to the trees and their reflections in the water.

We will cycle the plateau and visit sites on the way inc Buddha statues and Cool Pool 

We will stay tonight at the Rock Viewpoint

Cycle 60km', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (932, 38, 'Day 7: Konglor Cave — Cave', 'moderate', 'Konglor cave(B, L,D) 

A 40km cycle ride through a karst limestone valley to a 7km long water cave 
Getting into a long wooden boat (called a sampan) with an outboard motor, your guide will take you through 7.5 kilometres of an underground river as it twists and turns far below the earth’s surface until you emerge back into the daylight at a few remote villages. During the first part of the trip through the cave, you will stop at a short walking section where the jagged stalactites, stalagmites, and other cave features are illuminated. Otherwise, the cave is pitch black, lit only by your headlamp.

We can take the bikes through and cycle the other side and stay at Ban Natane before returning to our Resort. In Nahin

This is the highlight of the loop 

Cycle 60km', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (933, 38, 'Day 8: Nahin — Temple', 'easy', 'Nahin -Veintiane (B,L,D)

Transfer to the city along the main road and arrive in the city at 280km, stopping on the riverside for lunch at Paksan. We will arrive in the Capital at around 33 pm, and if time permits us can visit the Buddha Park.

We will take an evening ride around the capital, visiting the major attractions, Patuaxay  Arch and That Luang Temple. Dinner will be a local-style BBq on the shores of the Mighty Mekong. 

Transfer 280km ride 25km', 'ACTIVE', NOW());

