INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (951, 39, 'Day 1: Arrive Luang Prabang — Exploration', 'easy', 'ARRIVE LUANG PRABANG (D)
We will collect you at the Airport and transfer you to your hotel.

A welcome dinner and tour briefing at Khaiphaen a local vocational training restaurant that trains marginalised youth for careers in hospitality from the surrounding villages. 
 
Enjoy the evening, unwind and explore this true Gem of a city. The peninsula in the confluence of the Nam Khan River and the Mekong offers a fantastic backdrop to this unforgettable adventure. 
Overnight Luang Prabang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (952, 39, 'Day 2: Luang Prabang — Bike', 'moderate', 'LUANG PRABANG - PAKXANG (B) 

Today begins with a bike fitting following breakfast, after which we’ll set off for our first ride of the trip. 
We start the ride along the peaceful tarmac route to get accustomed to riding in Laos before we hit the harder dirt roads. It''s a comfortable day riding through rural villages to the small town of Pakxang
Easy', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1032, 39, 'Day 82: Overnight Paxang — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Overnight Paxang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (953, 39, 'Day 3: Pak Xeng — Exploration', 'easy', 'PAK XENG - VIENG KHAM (B)
From Pakxeng the road gets tough a Dirt Country highway along the Nam Xang river takes you through  Khmu Villages and banana plantations to the village of Vieng Kham This challenging first day outside of the city and an exciting taste of things to come! a night in a local guesthouse and great hospitality from the locals is rewarded.

This is a hard day''s ride.  Distance 77km Dirt Road 
Overnight in a Viengkham', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (954, 39, 'Day 4: Vieng Kham — Bike', 'moderate', 'VIENG KHAM - MUANG NGOI (B)
A Short transfer in the morning takes us to the start of the trail to Sleepy Muang Ngoi, the road is seldom travelled by bike and is a real treat for cyclists. This road has many villages with no running water or power from the Hmong, Khmu and Leu minorities
Transfer 15km. Distance 46km Dirt Road  Single Trail
Overnight in Muang Ngoi', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (955, 39, 'Day 5: Muang Ngoi — Temple', 'moderate', 'MUANG NGOI - MUANG KHUA (B) 
Today we transfer to the river to board a traditional long boat for the cruise up the Nam Ou river to the entrance to Phongsaly district. We call in at the Sleepy town of Muang Ngoi on the way to stretch our legs to visit the temple and the cave complex used as shelter during the 2nd Indochina war. 
Overnight in Muang Khua', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (956, 39, 'Day 6: Muang Khua — Exploration', 'moderate', 'MUANG KHUA - NAGNANG HOMESTAY (B)
We start the morning with a very steep climb as we head south through the Maung Khua district this road has some great views for miles over the province. the final stage of this day is an even and steady 20km ride to the Leu Minority Village, Nagnang. 
We can meet our homestay families and later before dinner the village will perform a Baci ceremony to say thank you for the visit and to wish us luck on our onward journey
Challenging', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1020, 39, 'Day 70: Overnight In Nagnang — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Overnight in Nagnang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (957, 39, 'Day 7: Nagnang — Boat', 'moderate', 'NAGNANG - HARPANG(B)
Leaving the Lue Village, we continue south for 10km before meeting the tarmac for 19km to Nong Khiaw, a boat awaits to take us to the drop-off point one hour down the Nam Ou River. We then follow the narrow trail 20km along the water''s edge. The Van will meet us at the main road for a 20-minute transfer to the Guesthouse in Harpang

Transfer 10km 
Distance 49km ( 30km Dirt Road,  19km Tarmac) 

Overnight in Harpang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (958, 39, 'Day 8: Harpang — Boat', 'easy', 'HARPANG - LATHAN - LUANG PRABANG (B)
Start with a short transfer to the beginning of the mud trail in the Village of Houaylae. 
Our final dirt trail is another challenging ride and climb for the first 17km. The road is open and lush arable farmland. 
Expect the locals to have a great deal of interest in you as this is well off the tourist trail even though we are only 45 km from Luang Prabang. 
A Traditional Longtail Boat will be moored in the Village of Lathan and we can cruise back to the City down the Mighty Mekong 
Distance 55 km.  Single-Track Dirt Road 
Overnight in Luang Prabang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());

-- ===== NORTHERN HEIGHTS [BIKINGCYCLING (30)] =====
INSERT INTO destinations (id, country_id, name, status, created_at) VALUES (40, 1, 'Luang Prabang', 'ACTIVE', NOW()) ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE name=VALUES(name);
INSERT INTO tours (
    id, destination_id, sku, title, duration, price,
    summary, hightlight, included, not_included, status, created_at
) VALUES (
    40, 40, NULL, 'Northern Heights',
    '10 DAYS', 2895,
    'As our adventure comes to a close, we reflect on the breathtaking landscapes, the warmth of the local cultures, and the camaraderie shared among fellow travellers. This journey through Northern Thailand and Laos has been a tapestry of experiences woven with nature, wildlife, history, and heart—each pedal stroke bringing unforgettable memories and the spirit of adventure alive', 'Chiang Mai Night Bazaar
Slow Boat on the Mekong 
Enchanting Teak Forest Ride
UNESCO World Heritage town of Luang Prabang
Ethnic Minority Villages and Waterfalls
Mountain Landscapes and Sceneries
Stunning green valley and limestone karsts of Vang Vieng
Total Cycling: 545km',
    '- All sightseeing as described in program above
- Transportation in private a /c vehicle and one truck for support 
- All Accommodation in hotels (Twin or Double), Homestays and Guesthouses
- English speaking guide
- Mechanic to maintain bikes
- Meals: B= breakfast, L= lunch, D= dinner as stated by each day itinerary
- Lao PDR governmental tax and service charge
- Luggage handling
- All Boat Transfers
- Airport Pick up and drop off 
- Bike, Helmet Rental
- $25 per person donation to Pedal For Purpose , Fairtrek Community tourism programs', '- All sightseeing as described in program above
- Transportation in private a /c vehicle and one truck for support 
- All Accommodation in hotels (Twin or Double), Homestays and Guesthouses
- English speaking guide
- Mechanic to maintain bikes
- Meals: B= breakfast, L= lunch, D= dinner as stated by each day itinerary
- Lao PDR governmental tax and service charge
- Luggage handling
- All Boat Transfers
- Airport Pick up and drop off 
- Bike, Helmet Rental
- $25 per person donation to Pedal For Purpose , Fairtrek Community tourism programs',
    'ACTIVE', NOW()
);
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (976, 40, 'Day 1: Our Adventure Begins As We Gather At The Chiang Mai Airport — Bike', 'moderate', 'Our adventure begins as we gather at the Chiang Mai airport, the air buzzing. We check into our cosy accommodation, where the friendly staff briefs us about our thrilling journey ahead, ensuring our bikes are perfectly fitted for the adventure. With eager hearts, we embark on our first ride, a gentle path alongside the serene Ping River. The rhythm of the pedals invites us to soak in Thailand''s vibrant sights and sounds. Our first stop, Ban Tawai, a charming arts and crafts hub, offers a delightful opportunity to browse for unique souvenirs before we return to the lively ambience of Chiang Mai.
Ride: 40 km
Overnight in Chiang Mai.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (977, 40, 'Day 2: After A Hearty Breakfast — Waterfall', 'moderate', 'After a hearty breakfast, we embark on a scenic transfer to a tranquil reservoir. A boat carries us to the trailhead, where we plunge into an outstanding ride through a lush teak forest. The singletrack trail weaves through the trees, each twist and turn revealing breathtaking views. We’re treated to a magnificent waterfall where our support team awaits with refreshing drinks and snacks. Energised, we ride on to a quaint restaurant overlooking the reservoir for lunch. In the afternoon, we explore country back roads, eventually cutting through dense forest until we arrive at our resort near Chiang Dao. A dip in the pool is the perfect way to wind down after a day of exploration.
Ride: 60 km
Overnight in Chiang Dao.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (978, 40, 'Day 3: Today — Cave', 'moderate', 'Today, we transfer to the mystical Chiang Dao Caves, the gateway to our striking ride. We pedal through expansive rice fields and under towering limestone cliffs, transitioning to dirt roads crafted by local hill tribes. The vibrant Akha, Lisu, Lau, and Palaung communities welcome us with their colourful traditions; we may even catch sight of Palaung women adorned with ornate brass jewellery. A leisurely lunch at a Forestry Camp rejuvenates us before we embark on memorable mountain trails. As the day concludes, our support team transports us to Chiang Rai.
Ride: 48 km
Overnight in Chiang Rai.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (979, 40, 'Day 4: After Breakfast — Temple', 'moderate', 'After breakfast, we cycle 14 km along picturesque dirt roads to the stunning Wat Rong Khun, known as the White Temple. Its dazzling architecture shines brilliantly in the sunlight, leaving us in awe. Leaving Chiang Rai, we follow the tranquil Kok River, surrounded by lush plantations. Our journey leads us to Chiang Saen, a historic town that hugs the Mekong River, where we spend the afternoon soaking in the sights from a viewpoint in the heart of the Golden Triangle.
Ride: 65 km
Overnight in Chiang Saen.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (980, 40, 'Day 5: The Day Begins With An Easy Ride Along The Mekong River — Exploration', 'moderate', 'The day begins with an easy ride along the Mekong River, framed by majestic mountain backdrops and quaint hill tribe villages. As we ride through tobacco and rice fields, the landscape transforms into a tapestry of natural beauty. The last 12 kilometres challenge us with steep ascents, igniting our adventurous spirit. We arrive in Chiang Khong, the gateway to Laos, filled with reflections on our time in Thailand.
Ride: 67 km
Overnight in Chiang Khong.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (981, 40, 'Day 6: Post Breakfast — Boat', 'moderate', 'Post breakfast, we transfer to the pier for our journey into Laos. Our guide greets us warmly and assists with the border crossing. We board a private boat that glides down the Mekong River, an authentic lunch served onboard as we embrace the tranquillity of our surroundings. Keep your camera ready; this journey is filled with picture-perfect scenery. Upon arrival in Pakbeng, we settled into our riverside accommodation, lulled by the gentle rhythms of the river.

Overnight in Pakbeng.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (982, 40, 'Day 7: A One — Exploration', 'moderate', 'A one-hour transfer brings us to the heart of rural Laos, where we cycle past hill tribe villages that thrive off the land. The friendly locals greet us as we pass through villages populated by the Phu Tai, Tai Lu, Hmong, Tai Dam, Lao, and Khamu. Our journey takes us through weaving villages, where families craft their traditions on ancient looms. A challenging 300-meter climb rewards us with stunning views as we descend into Oudomxay, the provincial capital.
Ride: 80 km
Overnight in Nam Kat Yorla Pa resort Oudomxay.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (983, 40, 'Day 8: We Dive Back Into Adventure As We Traverse The Rugged Terrain — Exploration', 'moderate', 'We dive back into adventure as we traverse the rugged terrain, surrounded by the rich greenery of the limestone mountains and forests. This day offers exhilarating hills, leading to breathtaking views before the road smooths out, unfolding into a beautiful landscape. The highlight is the thrilling 30 km downhill ride to Pak Mong, a charming depot town nestled in the hills. Energized by the day’s exertions, we continue onwards to Nong Khiaw, our destination for the night. A well-deserved dip in the resort pool, set against the breathtaking backdrop of Elephant Head Mountain, provides the perfect conclusion to a day filled with challenge and beauty.
Ride: 120 km
Overnight in Nong Khiaw.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (984, 40, 'Day 9: Today Promises A Spectacular Journey As We Set Out On A Boat Ride Along The Serene Nam Ou River — Waterfall', 'moderate', 'Today promises a spectacular journey as we set out on a boat ride along the serene Nam Ou River, leading us to a small Lao village. The tranquillity of the river sets the tone for our adventure ahead. We lace up our hiking boots and prepare to discover the stunning 100 Waterfalls. As we stroll through verdant jungles and over small streams, the symphony of cascading water beckons us closer. The scene is mesmerizing—nature at its most stunning. Our guide leads us to hidden corners, where we can splash in refreshing pools and enjoy a locally prepared lunch amidst the cascades. We wind our way back to the valley via a small villager’s trail, taking in panoramic views of the Nam Ou valley and floating back to the town. 


Overnight in Nong Khiaw.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (985, 40, 'Day 10: Our Final Cycling Day Begins With A Tranquil Boat Ride On The Nam Ou River — Boat', 'moderate', 'Our final cycling day begins with a tranquil boat ride on the Nam Ou River, setting the stage for an unforgettable journey. The roads today are smoother, allowing us to revel in the stunning landscapes that unfold as we cycle alongside the river. Surrounded by majestic mountain ranges, we navigate minor passes that add a touch of adventure to our ride. As we approach Luang Prabang, we pass through lush teakwood plantations, a final reminder of the region''s natural beauty. We celebrate the end of our journey with dinner at a local vocational training restaurant, supporting marginalised youth, followed by a stroll through the vibrant night market, soaking in the beautiful atmosphere before retreating to our accommodation for the night.
Ride: 65 km
Overnight in Luang Prabang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());

