INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1101, 45, 'Day 1: Chiang Mai — Bike', 'moderate', 'Chiang Mai (B, L)
We meet at the Hotel after Breakfast to brief everyone thoroughly and make sure the bikes fit. Then, we take a short transfer out of town and start a nice, easy ride along the Ping River to get accustomed to
riding in Thailand. Our stopping point of Ban Tawai is the arts and crafts area and we have time
to browse the stalls for souvenirs before heading back to Chiang Mai.

Ride: 40 km (about 25 miles)
Accommodation: Ratana Hotel (Standard Room)
Overnight in Chiang Mai', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1102, 45, 'Day 2: The Teak Forest Ride — Waterfall', 'moderate', 'The Teak Forest Ride (B, L) 
After breakfast we transfer to the nearby reservoir where we take a boat to our trailhead. We
ride an outstanding trail through a scenic teak forest enjoying some great single track. We eventually
spill out of the forest at a waterfall where our support truck is waiting to replenish water supplies
and provide a snack. We then ride on road to our lunch stop, a great little restaurant overlooking
a reservoir. After lunch we ride along country back roads before cutting off road and riding
through the forest. We then transfer to our resort near Chiang Dao. Time to enjoy the swimming
pool before dinner.

Ride: 60 km (about 37 miles)
Accommodation: Marisa Resort (Kasalong Superior)
Overnight in Chiang Dao', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1103, 45, 'Day 3: Chiang Dao To Chiang Rai — Cave', 'moderate', 'Chiang Dao to Chiang Rai (B, L)
We make a short transfer from the resort to Chiang Dao Caves and the start of our ride. Today’s
ride is a real treat for mountain bikers. We ride through rice fields and among soaring limestone
cliffs before hitting the dirt. We ride dirt roads cut by local hill tribes and we will meet Akha, Lisu,
Lau and Palaung peoples. The colorful Palaung are recent migrants and you will see their women
adorned with heavy brass waistbands working the fields. We stop for lunch at a Forestry Camp
before a memorable afternoon riding some quite outstanding mountain trails. Our support vehicle
will be waiting at the trail end to transport us two hours to Chiang Rai.

Ride: 48 km (about 30 miles)
Accommodation: Pan Kled Villa Eco Hill Resort (Superior Room)

Overnight in Chiang Rai', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1104, 45, 'Day 4: Chiang Rai To Chiang Saen — Temple', 'moderate', 'Chiang Rai to Chiang Saen (B, L)
After breakfast, we cycle 14 km along dirt roads flanked by rice paddies to Chiang Rai''s spectacular white temple, Wat Rong Khun. Make sure you have your sunglasses on as we take in the splendour of one of Thailand''s most famous edifices. 

After leaving Chiang Rai, you follow the Kok River north through fruit plantations and paddies. 

Chiang Saen, the oldest urban settlement of Thailand and former capital of the Lanna Kingdom, is in a beautiful location on the banks of the Mekong River.

 In the afternoon, you can visit the viewpoint in the heart of the Golden Triangle.

Ride: 65 km (about 39 miles)
Accommodation: A Hotel Simply (Superior Garden view)

Overnight in Chiang Saen', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1105, 45, 'Day 5: Chiang Saen To Chiang Khong — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Chiang Saen to Chiang Khong (B, L)

The first stage of today’s ride is easy going. With mountain backdrops, the road follows the
Mekong river through picturesque hill tribe villages, tobacco and rice fields. 

The last 12 kilometers are more challenging, with some steep but short ascents. 

The road joins the main road just before the entry to Chiang Khong, the border entry to Laos. 

This is the last night that you will stay in Thailand on this tour.

Ride: 67 km (about 42 miles)
Accommodation: Chiang Khong Teak Garden River View Hotel (Superior Room)
Overnight in Chiang Khong Resort Hotel', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1106, 45, 'Day 6: Chiang Khong — Boat', 'moderate', 'Chiang Khong-Laos (Huay Xai to Pakbeng) (B, L)
After breakfast, we transfer you to the pier for your journey to Pakbeng. The Thai  team
will leave after dropping you off at the checkpoint and the Laos Team will guide you through to the crossing and on to the pier where a traditional mekong long boat will be waiting for you
Travel by boat down the Mekong: rest and relax. Take a good book and lots of food as the journey is about 8 hours 
Accommodation: Mekong Riverside Bungalows Hotel
Overnight in Pakbeng', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1107, 45, 'Day 7: Pakbeng To Oudomxay — Exploration', 'easy', 'Pakbeng to Oudomxay (B, L)
After a one-hour transfer, we are cycling in very rural Laos, an area inhabited by hill tribe villages who eke a meagre existence from the land. Along the way, you will pass villages of Phu Tai, Tai Lu, Hmong, Tai Dam, Lao and Khamu. 
The people are very friendly and not yet tired of seeing tourists. We stop at weaving villages along the way, where you still see families sitting in the shade weaving on old looms. After climbing a 300-meter pass, a long descent brings you to Oudomxay, the capital of the Oudomxay Province.

Jump in the Van to circumvent the city then cycle the last 15 km to Nam Kat Yoral Pa a beautiful resort on the banks of the Kat River

Ride: 80 KM (about 50 miles)
Accommodation: Namkat Yorla Pa (ECO room)

Overnight in Oudomxay', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1108, 45, 'Day 8: Oudomxay To Nong Khiaw — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Oudomxay to Nong Khiaw (B, L)
We''ll head back into the jungle for stretches of this spectacular route; although hilly, it soon gives way to gentler gradient and opens to magnificent scenery and finally a 30 km downhill ride to Pak Mong, a small Quaint depot town. from here it is a beautiful ride to Nong Khiaw. This is one of the more difficult days of the trip, so push yourself you will be rewards with a night’s rest at a resort, riverside bungalow and a dip in the pool underneath Elephant head mountain.

Ride: 120 KM (about 74 miles)
Accommodation: Phaxang Resort  (Standard)

Overnight in Nong Khiaw', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1109, 45, 'Day 9: Nong Khiaw — Waterfall', 'challenging', 'Nong Khiaw 100 waterfalls trek (B, L)
Nam Ou River Cruise, 100 Waterfall Trek.
Start the day with a peaceful boat ride on the Nam Ou River. Along the way, you''ll be able to explore a small Lao village along the river. Then we''ll hike through small streams and rice paddies to reach the base of the 100 waterfalls. 
For the following few hours, you''ll see only water and jungle and hear the sound of clear waterfall cascades. Your guide will lead you through the cascades and prepare a local-style lunch on the falls in the middle of it all. 
A small villagers’ trail on the top of the 100 waterfalls will lead us back down into the valley, offering wide views over the landscapes of the Nam Ou valley along the way. Hiking back to the village we will have more time to see the daily life.
Accommodation: Phaxang Resort  (Standard)
Overnight in Nong Khiaw', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1110, 45, 'Day 10: Nong Khiaw — Boat', 'moderate', 'Nong Khiaw - Luang Prabang (B, L, D)
A private boat on the Nam Ou river to take you to the starting point of flatter and better roads today that will enable you to complete the longer distance to Luang Prabang. 

Only a few minor passes have to be climbed before you''re cycling along the banks of the Nam Ou river with stunning views of huge mountain ranges. On the last stage of the day, you''ll be cycling through teakwood plantations before arriving in Luang Prabang.’

Dinner at a local Vocational Training restaurant for marginalized youth and a stroll through the night market before retiring the night

Ride: 95 KM (about 59 miles)
Accommodation: Sala Prabang
Overnight in Luang Prabang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1111, 45, 'Day 11: Kuang Si Waterfalls — Waterfall', 'moderate', 'Kuang Si Waterfalls (B,L)
A one and a half hour trip to Kuang Si falls for a dip in the brilliant blue ice-cold waters is a must see in Laos. Luang Prabang remains one of Asia''s most beautiful historic towns, earning it the status of a World Heritage Site in 1995. and the falls are the biggest attraction. 
On  the return leg we will call in at Laos Buffalo dairy for a tour and a water buffalo selfie! this amazing project helps to train locals in animal nutrition and welfare and produces the best Ice Cream in Laos

Ride: 60 KM 
Accommodation: Sala Prabang
Overnight in Luang Prabang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1112, 45, 'Day 12: Departure Day — Exploration', 'easy', 'Departure Day 
Free to Explore the city before transfer to the Airport in plenty of time for you onward flight', 'ACTIVE', NOW());

