INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1151, 47, 'Day 1: Hanoi — Exploration', 'easy', 'HANOI - HUE

Arrive in Hanoi and spend the day enjoying the sites of the city we will collect you in town then transfer to the train station for the Night Train to Hue 
Arrive in Hue this morning and begin cycling through town, across the Perfume River and to Hue''s Imperial Citadel. Explore the sprawling complex, rich with history, on foot before continuing the ride out to the countryside along dirt tracks to the Mausoleums of Tu Duc and Khai Dinh. Ride past relics and ruins until you reach the end of your journey at the beautiful Thien Mu Pagoda. Overnight in Hue.

After Lunch, we will Cycle to the Lagoon to explore the eco-tourism zone and take a trip to a stilted restaurant to enjoy cold drinks and fresh seafood 

45KM+ CYCLING (B, L, D)', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1152, 47, 'Day 2: Hue — Exploration', 'easy', 'HUE - A LUOI 
50KM+ CYCLING (B, L, D)

To start your lifetime’s adventure - we will pick you up before 9 am from Hue City, a celebrated place with royal connections and a key battleground during the 1968 Tet Offensive. After about an hour’s transfer by private bus, you will begin cycling. This is your first glimpse of the historic Ho Chi Minh Trail, now a peaceful location in the heart of our countryside and blessed with dense jungle. We head to A Luoi, where we stay the night, amidst one of the most fought-over areas during the war. In the distance Hamburger Hill is a battle conducted in 1969 and captured in the Hollywood film of 1987; a short visit can be arranged if you would like to see it.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1153, 47, 'Day 3: A Luoi — Exploration', 'moderate', 'A LUOI - KHE SANH 
60KM CYCLING (B, L, D)

Today you will cycle north down the A Shau Valley; the location of a key entry point from Lao into South Vietnam which fed battles in and around Hue. This is a great way to start the day with fresh air, rural villages and the chance to meet local people. After around 20km we will take you off-road to Long Hill Pass. This is an area of lush dense forest, stunning vistas and rugged mountains. Upon arriving at the summit you will be invited to have fresh tropical fruits and soft drinks. After cycling downhill and along the river to A Luoi town, you will enjoy lunch. In the afternoon, there is a 15km cycle through picturesque scenery, before you are transferred by bus to Khe Sanh – where you will visit the museum which commemorates the famed Battle of Khe Sanh.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1154, 47, 'Day 4: Khe Sanh — Exploration', 'moderate', 'KHE SANH - LAO BAO BORDER – XEPON
NO CYCLING (B, L, D)

Today you can relax as we drive you along Route 9 to the Lao border. Here you will meet our Lao team who will support the next phase of your remarkable journey. Route 9 was built during the French colonial period. In 1971, it saw Operation Lam Son 719, the aim of which was to cut the Trail using South Vietnamese forces, with the US providing logistics, aerial and artillery support. You will transfer to Xepon, via Ban Dong, both of which saw high levels of fighting. 

Yet your experience will not be that of war but of the tranquil Lao ways and the idyllic countryside, nevertheless – you will feel a temperature change, the saying goes – when the wind blows in Lao it burns everything in its path!

In the Afternoon we will arrange a meeting at the UXO centre to learn about the hazardous work required to clean up the countryside of unexploded ordnance that was dropped over a 9-year bombing campaign. The impact of the war on the people of Laos i still being felt today.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1155, 47, 'Day 5: Xepon — Exploration', 'moderate', 'XEPON - SARAVANE  - TAD LO 
85 KM CYCLING 
Meals (B, L, D)

This is the longest and hardest day of the trip 
                            
After breakfast, we will transfer and then south into rural Lao. The forested hills and the occasional village make it a peaceful atmosphere. The first big town is Muang Nong on the banks of the Nam Se Lanong. 

We continue  on the Ho Chi Minh trail until we reach Muang Ta Oy  and transfer by van through Saravnae 

This is a remote part of the country yet the Trail here saw much activity with Saravane town itself being destroyed. This day is tough and in the evening you will be treated to some traditional local drink of Lao Lao to celebrate your achievement.

We end the day at Tad Lo Lodge', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1156, 47, 'Day 6: Tad Lo Waterfalls Cycle To Sekong — Waterfall', 'moderate', 'Tad Lo Waterfalls Cycle to Sekong 
75KM CYCLING 
Meals (B, L, D)
                   
In the early morning light, we can visit the beautiful waterfalls and take a dip in chilly waters before we start our day ride to Sekong. This is a new provincial region, built in the 1980s, and is a sleepy backwater on the banks of the Sekong River. 

Your day through the province of Sekong will be calm and fascinating as it has a low population but is the most ethnically diverse area in Lao, with some 14 different groups. In the evening you can try some local food and Lao Hai, alcohol in a jar, where water turns into wine!', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1157, 47, 'Day 7: Sekong To Attapeu — Boat', 'moderate', 'SEKONG TO ATTAPEU 
Cycling 0km 
Meals (B, L, D)

Up at Dawn to board local 3-man fishing boats to get a real taste of river life. we will amble our way down the river for calling at a village on the way. 
We will need long sleeves and lots of sunscreens as the boats are open-topped. 
we will meet the vans and stop at Don Chan for a riverside lunch.  before continuing an optional 25km by the river to Xakhe if time permits. 

from Xakhe it is 30km by road to Attapeu.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1158, 47, 'Day 8: Attapeu — Exploration', 'moderate', 'ATTAPEU - BO Y BORDER - DAK TO 
65KM CYCLING (B, L, D) 

Attapeu town is nestled on the banks of the Sekong River and from here you cycle back over the Truong Son Mountain Range into South Vietnam. This is one of the most memorable parts of the Trail. When you travel towards Vietnam you will understand why this area is called the “Roof of Lao” - high mountain peaks, deep valleys and vast forested panoramas; with few visitors nature carries you through. 

Our Vietnamese representative will welcome you at the border, and transfer you to Dak To; a location of a former US airbase and several major battles.  Here you will dine with the group, reflecting on your great Lao achievements.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1159, 47, 'Day 9: Dak To — Exploration', 'moderate', 'DAK TO - PLEIKU 
60KM CYCLING (B,L,D)

After an early breakfast, we visited US Phoenix Airfield and later Rocket Ridge, a giant escarpment where the US built Fire Bases including Charlie Hill, to stop the flow of traffic down the Trail. Pleiku is your next destination, which has some of the best coffee in Vietnam. As you cycle through a wide valley, surrounded by mountains, dotted with tea and coffee plantations, there will be the opportunity to visit the Jarai and Bhanar minority villages. Their communal houses, with very steep and tall roofs, are of great pride to each village because they define the regional landscape. 

Pleiku itself was an airbase, and in the spring of 1975, it was attacked to see if the US would return. When there was no action, there could be a push to take Buon Ma Thuot.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1160, 47, 'Day 10: Pleiku To Buon Ma Thuot — Exploration', 'moderate', 'PLEIKU TO BUON MA THUOT 
70KM CYCLING (B, L, D)

Today you cycle a historic route. In 1975 the region became a vital part of the Battle of Buon Ma Thuot and soon after saw the launch of the Ho Chi Minh Campaign which led to the fall of Saigon. After breakfast, you have a short transfer from the hotel to where you will start cycling.

From here you will ride for 30km through rolling hills, coffee plantations and small villages before turning off onto an offbeat backroad. For 25km this backroad goes through stunning rubber plantations to a backdrop of small rolling hills. 

The last 10km is on a beautiful rural road that eventually widens and wanders through small farms and villages. A picnic-style lunch will be taken on the way. At the end of the cycle, there will be a 6km transfer to the hotel in Buon Me Thuot.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1161, 47, 'Day 11: Buon Ma Thuot — Exploration', 'easy', 'BUON MA THUOT - DONG XOAI - HCMC 
60KM CYCLING (B, L, D)

We left Buon Me Thuot by bus in the early morning, saying goodbye to the biggest coffee city in Vietnam then immersed ourselves in the famous Ho Chi Minh trail and its magnificent scenery. Our stops today include visits to rubber, pepper, coffee, and curry plantations. We will get as close as it gets to the Cambodian border on the real war remnants'' HCM trail. 

In the evening light,', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1162, 47, 'Day 12: Dong Xoai — Exploration', 'easy', 'DONG XOAI - CHON THANH - CU CHI - HO CHI MINH CITY 
20KM CYCLING (B,L)

This is your great victory day as you cycle from Dong Xoai to Chon Thanh, the endpoint of Truong Son – the Ho Chi Minh Trail. 

We spent a little time at the monument erected at Chon Thanh crossroads to mark the endpoint, located in front of the People''s Committee of Chon Thanh. During a 3-hour transfer to Cu Chi tunnels, lunch is served. At Cu Chi, we learn how people fought using simple weapons, as well as going down into the small tunnels dug by the Viet Cong. After learning the history here, we continue our driving toward Ho Chi Minh City. 

This is where your lifetime’s adventure concludes upon arrival at your hotel congratulations you have conquered the Trail.

*Itinerary is subject to change depending on road conditions and availability of rooms*', 'ACTIVE', NOW());

