INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1251, 51, 'Day 1: Luang Prabang — Waterfall', 'moderate', 'Luang Prabang - Kuang Si Falls Round trip (B, L)

Our first Ride is an easy ride to the must-see waterfall in northern Laos. The azure-blue waters and 3-tiered cascades are a big attraction, and no visit to Luang Prabang is complete without a refreshing dip in the water. 
On the way to the falls, we will visit a local Buffalo Dairy and learn about this fantastic program that provides economic support Cycle 50km to local villages and teaches farmers about animal health and welfare. The Dairy produces some of Asia''s tastiest cheeses, and the Ice Cream is incredible! 
Don’t forget to get your Water Buffalo Selfie before hopping back on the saddle
Cycle 60km 
Overnight in Luang Prabang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1252, 51, 'Day 2: Luang Prabang — Boat', 'easy', 'Luang Prabang - Nong Khiaw (B, L)
Transfer for 40km outside of the city til the road opens along the banks of the Nam Ou river, follow the river for a while through jungle groves at the Nam Ou Dam we travel the dirt roads for 10km until we are picked up by a traditional narrow boat for the final hour boat ride to the sleepy town of Nong Khiaw. 
Tonight we sleep in a bungalow resort in the shadow of Elephant Head Mountain. 
Cycle 50km 

Transfer 1 Hour
Overnight in Nong Khiaw', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1253, 51, 'Day 3: Nong Khiaw — Waterfall', 'challenging', 'Nong Khiaw 100 waterfalls trek (B, L)
You''ll start the day with a peaceful boat ride on the Nam Ou River. Along the way, you''ll be able to explore a small Lao village along the river. Then we''ll hike through small streams and rice paddies to reach the base of the 100 waterfalls.
For the following few hours, you''ll see only water and jungle and hear the sound of clear waterfall cascades. Your guide will lead you through the cascades and prepare a local-style lunch on the falls in the middle of it all.
A small villagers’ trail on the top of the 100 waterfalls will lead us back down into the valley, offering wide views over the landscapes of the Nam Ou valley along the way. 
The back on the boat to transfer back to the comfort of the Resort

Overnight in Nong Khiaw', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1254, 51, 'Day 4: Nong Khiaw — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Nong Khiaw - Vieng Kham - Muang Haim (B, L)
Today we start by going upstream to the Village of Muang Ngoi, taking an hour to wander the sleepy main street. Before we start riding the dirt roads through the mountains, passing remote villages well off the beaten path. 
On our arrival back on the main road, we can transfer for 2.5 hours to the village of Muang Haim on the edge of the largest nature reserve in Laos.
Cycle 50km 
Overnight in Muang Haim', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1255, 51, 'Day 5: Namet Phou Louey Night Safari — Boat', 'moderate', 'Namet Phou Louey Night Safari (B,L,D)
We drive from Muang Haim  to a small Khmu village, the gateway to the Nam Nern Night Safari. After a brief orientation, we set off upstream in traditional boats, guided by local villagers who share their knowledge of this stunning region. Arriving at the eco-lodge for lunch, we rest among the towering trees before continuing our journey upstream. As the sun sets, we gather for a fireside dinner, then venture out for a thrilling night of wildlife spotlighting amidst the sounds of the jungle. We retreat to our cosy Lao-style bungalow, the night alive with the calls of nature.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1256, 51, 'Day 6: Nam Et Phou Louey — Boat', 'moderate', 'Nam Et Phou Louey - Sam Neua (B, L) 
After spending the night in the eco-lodge located in the protected area forest, we will take a morning walk around the area where a local Khmu guide will explain medicinal plants and show you the remains of a centuries-old village.
After breakfast, we will go back downstream by boat to where we began the tour, 24 hours after in the national park
From here we will cycle ride transfer to the pretty small town of Sam Nuea 
Cycle 50-60km
Overnight in Sam Neua', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1257, 51, 'Day 7: Sam Nuea — Cave', 'easy', 'Sam Nuea - Vieng Xai  - Pu Luong (B, L) 
Our final day in Laos will be spent on the van as we have to reach the border by 11:00 am. A short transfer from Sam Neua in the morning will bring us to the Famous Viang Xai Caves. At first glance, Vieng Xai doesn’t look like much. 
The sparsely populated, sleepy village sits on a plain surrounded by hulking limestone karst. As unlikely as it may seem, the peaceful landscape played a pivotal role during the Secret War. Concealed in the rock are hundreds of caves, and for almost a decade, 20,000 soldiers and civilians survived the intense aerial bombing by living underground in this hidden city, which also served as the command centre for the Pathet Lao.
We’ll then continue to the border. At this point, we say goodbye to our Laos team and meet up with your new crew after crossing into Vietnam. The cycling from the border is wonderful but we will cycle about 40km to enjoy the spectacular scenes, then transfer to a beautiful lodge perched on the mountainside, where we spend the night.
40KM CYCLING
Overnight in Pu Luong', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1258, 51, 'Day 8: Pu Luong Nature Reserve — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Pu Luong Nature reserve - Cuc Phoung NP (B, L)

We leave early this morning to get a transfer to a suspension bridge over the Cham River, where you begin your walk passing the rice field to the stunning water wheels area. Get up close to each wheel and discover how water is moved from river to handmade bamboo aqueducts via simple constructions of all sizes. 
Arriving at a local fisherman’s house, you have a short rest to gear up for the rafting adventure. Float along the calm river and enjoy the views, in between learning how to paddle and steer your handcrafted bamboo rafts. 
At the scenic Tan Lap Bridge, you disembark and continue our biking toward Cuc Phuong. Arrive in Cuc Phuong National Park in the late afternoon. Overnight in Cuc Phuong, Vietnam''s first and largest national park.

50KM CYCLING
Transfer 2-3 hours
Overnight in Cuc Phuong', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1259, 51, 'Day 9: Cuc Phuong Np — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Cuc Phuong NP - Ria - Ghenh - Tam Coc (B, L)
Breakfast is in the park restaurant, and then it''s off to visit the Endangered Primate Rescue Centre. From there, the bus takes the group into the depths of the reserve. From the centre of the park, we''ll cycle along canopied forest trails and through the primitive jungle - an exclusive, tourist-free route, all the way to the gate of the national park. 
The day''s cycling continues onto Dong Giao – a pineapple plantation where you can enjoy fresh pineapple from local farmers selling on sideroad. We ride out of the plantation to Tam Diep Township, then continue to Tam Coc, where we spend the night.
60KM CYCLING
Overnight in Tam Coc-Ninh Binh.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1260, 51, 'Day 10: Ninh Binh Explorer — Cave', 'moderate', 'Ninh Binh Explorer (B, L)
Today is a day of relaxation. Take your time to explore the natural wonder of the area. We will take a rowing boat trip to explore the beauty of Tam Coc, known as "Halong Bay on Land". In one and a half hours on the boat, you are visiting the Ngo Dong River with three water tunnels, viewing the rice along both sides of the river, and taking photos of local farmers working and catching river food. Moving between the green high mountains, you feel as if you are living in the quiet and far further from modern life. We continue to Mua cave, which was constructed following the model of the "miniature Great Wall" in China with nearly 500 steps up to the mountain peak to see the most amazing panoramic view of the plateau. . 

Overnight in Ninh Binh', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1261, 51, 'Day 11: Ninh Binh — Boat', 'moderate', 'Ninh Binh - Hanoi (B, L)
In the morning we leave Ninh Binh for Kenh Ga, a tranquil floating village where we''ll take a boat trip to soak up the laid-back nature of the local villagers. 
Lunch at a local restaurant then we drive to Hanoi airport for your onward flight. 
20KM+ CYCLING
Transfer 2.5 Hours
Overnight in Hanoi', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1262, 51, 'Day 12: Hanoi To Halong Bay — Boat', 'easy', 'Hanoi to Halong Bay ( B, L, D )
Arrive in Ha Long City, and board our cruise for an overnight journey. Sip on a refreshing welcome drink upon check-in before you begin your cruise towards the southeast of Halong Bay, passing Fighting-Cock Islet. After lunch, we kayak around the Tung Sau area. Surrounded by cascading mountains that jut out from the jewel-coloured waters of the bay, this place is an isolated region of water in Halong used for pearl farming.
17:00 Return to the boat and freshen up for the evening’s activities. The bar opens for a Happy Hour promotion on a selection of drinks.
17:30 Join the exciting cooking or fruit carving demonstration on the sundeck (or in the restaurant, depending on the weather). Don’t miss out on the stunning view of the sunset over the enchanting Halong Bay from the sundeck of the boat.
19:15 Savour the delicious dinner in the restaurant.
20:45 Free time to enjoy a drink at the bar or stargaze on the sundeck. Or enjoy the squid fishing program after dinner on the first deck.
Retire to your cabin for a good night''s sleep.
Overnight in Ha Long Bay', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1263, 51, 'Day 13: Halong Bay Discovery — Cave', 'moderate', 'Halong Bay Discovery (B, L, D)
For the early risers join us for a Tai Chi session on the sun deck. Tai chi helps focus the mind and condition the body and there is no better environment to practice this than amongst the limestone peaks and islands. Breakfast, coffee or tea is served. 
08:15 Get on the rowing boats to visit the Luon Cave area while taking in the magnificent karsts and limestone mountains.
09:00 Return to the boat* and cruise to the next attraction
10:00 Sightseeing around Cua Van Floating Village, well-known for its location in the heart of Halong Bay, by kayak or traditional rowing boat. The area is considered one of the most beautiful destinations in the world by Travel & Leisure Magazine.
11:30 Back to the boat* and enjoy lunch while the boat cruises to the Trinh Nu area.
14:00 Time to relax and explore the Trinh Nu beach or visit Trinh Nu Cave - one of the finest sunlight-filled caves in Halong Bay, covering an area of 2,000m2 with stunning stalactites and stalagmites.
16:00 Return to the Bhaya boat for some time at leisure to relax and freshen up after the day’s excursions.
17:30 Enjoy the Happy Hour promotion on a selection of drinks. Leisurely sip a drink while being enchanted by the glorious sunset of Halong Bay.
Join the fruit carving demonstration carried out by our talented chefs.
19:15 Appreciate the exotic flavours of the dinner on the last night of cruising.
20:24 Free time to enjoy a drink on the sundeck or rest in the cabin. 
Overnight in Halong Bay', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1264, 51, 'Day 14: Halong Bay — Cave', 'moderate', 'Halong Bay – Hanoi (B, L)
07:00 A light breakfast is served in the restaurant. The boat cruises towards the centre of Halong Bay.
07:20 Avoid the morning crowd and explore Sung Sot Cave, the largest cave inside Halong Bay with 10,000 square meters of space that holds thousands of stalactites and stalagmites and is threaded by a 500-meter paved passageway.
08:20 Return to the boat and enjoy the brunch served in the restaurant.
09:30 Time to pack your luggage and get ready to check out. Enjoy the scenery as the boat cruises back to the port.
10:30 Disembark from the boat at Tuan Chau International Marina, where you take a shuttle bus back to Hanoi. A Free final Evening at leisure and overnight in Hanoi.
Overnight in Hanoi', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1265, 51, 'Day 15: Hanoi Departure  Day — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Hanoi Departure  Day  (B)
END OF SERVICES', 'ACTIVE', NOW());

