INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1276, 52, 'Day 1: Arrival In Luang Prabang — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Arrival in Luang Prabang (D)
Meet with our team for a short sunset ride around Luang Prabang to ensure we are confident about the journey ahead and to get acclimatized to life in SE Asia.  We will have an informal trip briefing and dinner at a local vocational training restaurant 
Khaiphaen Restaurant
Overnight in Luang Prabang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1277, 52, 'Day 2: Luang Prabang To Kuang Si Falls Round Trip — Waterfall', 'moderate', 'Luang Prabang to Kuang Si Falls Round Trip  (B, L)
Pack your Swimmers! This day is a great way to warm up for the ride ahead. Kuang Si Falls is the must-see natural wonder in northern Laos. We will swim in the azure blue cascading waterfalls is the perfect way to refresh yourself from a 30 km cycle ride. 

On the return to the town, we will call in at the Lao Buffalo Dairy to see how this Social enterprise is changing the lives of many villages. A picnic lunch including buffalo cheese will be served on the grounds.

Distance 60km
Overnight in Luang Prabang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1278, 52, 'Day 3: Luang Prabang To Nong Khiaw — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Luang Prabang to Nong Khiaw (B, L)
Overnight in Nong Khiaw', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1279, 52, 'Day 4: Nong Khiaw — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Nong Khiaw - Vieng Kham - Muang Ngoi (B,L)
​​The day from Nong Khiaw to Muang Ngoi promises to be the most challenging but also the most rewarding of the entire tour. The views are stunning as we pedal through the dense jungle and winding dirt roads. The lush greenery and stunning landscape create a sense of awe and wonder that is truly unforgettable. The communities along this route are equally fascinating, as they are off the beaten track and offer a glimpse into the traditional way of life in Laos. Meeting the van at the top of the dirt road and taking a short transfer into the village offers a chance to explore and immerse oneself in the local culture. The day promises to be filled with adventure, excitement, and the chance to create unforgettable memories.
Distance 80km
Overnight in Vieng Kham', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1280, 52, 'Day 5: Muang Ngoi — Boat', 'moderate', 'Muang Ngoi- Muang Khua (B, L)
Today we transfer to the river and a traditional long boat, for the beautiful trip up the Nam ou River, we will stop for a picnic lunch on the way, as we gently put our way upstream.  we arrive mid-afternoon in Muang Khua our last stop in Laos
Overnight in Muang Khua', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1281, 52, 'Day 6: Muang Khua To Dien Bien Phu — Exploration', 'easy', 'Muang Khua to Dien Bien Phu (B, L)
The Ride to the Vietnamese border is a straightforward ride over mountain passes. We will arrive at around lunchtime ready to cross and meet our Vietnam team and a 1-hour transfer to the Historically significant city of Dien Bien Phu take the afternoon and evening to explore this beautiful and fascinating city.
Ride 45km
Overnight in Dien Bien Phu', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1282, 52, 'Day 7: Dien Bien Phu — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Dien Bien Phu – Tuan Giao (B, L)
Cycling from Dien Bien Phu to Tuan Giao is an easy 80 km through many ethnic villages to Tuan Giao (one notable climb is a mountain pass 15 km outside Dien Bien). Overnight in a guesthouse. 
Distance  80km 
Overnight in Tuan Giao', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1283, 52, 'Day 8: Tuan Giao — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Tuan Giao – Son La (B, L)
Cycling from Tuan Giao to Son La. After a short transfer to the Pha Din pass (“Heaven and Earth” pass) to the summit of 1450 m, you will start the day with a 15 km downhill featuring a nice landscape of green rice fields and karst valley along the way. This stretch has light traffic, wandering water buffaloes, and Tai and Hmong children. Overnight in Hotel.
Distance 70km
Overnight in Son La', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1284, 52, 'Day 9: Son La — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Son La – Moc Chau (B, L)
After a short transfer, our day will be less hilly but no less spectacular, as we head off gradually downhill, our passage overshadowed by looming karst cliffs. After lunch, we''ll continue through lush, terraced rice paddies against the jagged cliff backdrop. 
Distance 45km
Overnight in Moc Chau', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1285, 52, 'Day 10: Moc Chau — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Moc Chau – Mai Chau (B, L)
After a hearty breakfast, we set off on a testing but spectacular day. Cycling along a narrow, quiet back road we''ll head into a region predominantly populated by Black Tai (Tai Dam) minority cultures. As we near Mai Chau, situated at 1000m, we pass through plum orchards and corn and tea plantations. Overnight in homestay.
Distance 45km
Overnight in Mai Chau', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1286, 52, 'Day 11: Mai Chau — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Mai Chau – Cuc Phuong  (B, L)
Following the banks of the Ma River, this day will be an easy one. The scenery, however, is timeless and photo opportunities abound as you pedal through a working landscape of people and crops. In the late afternoon, you will get a transfer to Cuc Phuong National Park. Cuc Phuong is one of Vietnam''s most important nature reserves and contains the country''s largest area of primary forest. Visit the Primate Rescue Centre and learn about the plight of endangered species such as the Cat Ba Langur. Overnight in Bungalow.
Distance 80km
Overnight in Cuc Phuong', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1287, 52, 'Day 12: Cuc Phuong — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Cuc Phuong -Hanoi (B)

Today your guide will be needed for another tour in Hanoi. your van a driver will help you ride the final leg to Hanoi. The ride is 40 km through Cuc Phuong forest to the park centre and a break for tea before taking a transfer to Hanoi. 
Overnight in Hanoi', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
