INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1301, 53, 'Day 1: Luang Prabang — Temple', 'moderate', 'Luang Prabang (D)
We meet at the airport then check in to our accommodation to brief everyone thoroughly and make sure the bikes fit.  We can take an hour or two if time permits to explore the Unesco Zone by bike and perhaps take in some of the Temples and the Hmong Night Market. 
Dinner is served at a local Vocational training Restaurant that provides exquisite food and employment opportunities to marginalized youth. Ride: 20km

Overnight in Luang Prabang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1302, 53, 'Day 2: Luang Prabang — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Luang Prabang - Phou Khoun (B)
The day begins with a 1 hour transfer to get over the first mountain, after 65km in a van we begin our mountain top ride to a simple guesthouse and a local restaurant. High in the mountains in the cross road town of Phoukhoun.
Overnight in PhouKhoun', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1303, 53, 'Day 3: Phou Khoun — Exploration', 'easy', 'Phou Khoun - Phonsavan (B,L)
This  road is known for big climbs and challenging riding. 
The views are spectacular from the limestone peaks as we enter the high plateau of Xiang Khouang Province, we stay the night in Phonsavan, a rapidly  developing destination . There is a lot of road to cover this day so a Transfer is used to begin the ride and a short van ride into the city at the end of the day is necessary.

Ride:  80 km 
Overnight in Phonsavan', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1304, 53, 'Day 4: Plain Of Jars Round Trip — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Plain Of Jars Round Trip (B,L)
This is a perfect ride to get used to the new climate as we are over 1000 meters above sea level. The Plain of Jars remains a place whose mysterious past has led to diverse speculations. Why did people make these amazing stone formations and what were they used for? 
Ride: 65 km 
Overnight in Phonsavan', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1305, 53, 'Day 5: Phonsavan — Exploration', 'easy', 'Phonsavan - Muang Khoun- Thathom(B,L)
We leave the city by van and begin our ride south, we begin the Ride at That Foun a 16th century Buddhist stupa situated on a remote plain, from here we cycle 90km on challenging mountain roads to the little town of Thathom. 
Overnight in Thathom', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1306, 53, 'Day 6: Thatthom — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Thatthom - Khoun Kham (B,L,D)
From Xiang Khounang to Bolikhamxay province in the shadow of Nam Kadding forest. We travel by van and bicycle to the village of Ban Nahin  and a welcoming riverside guesthouse and the best red curry in the province! 
Cycle 80km
Overnight in Ban Nahin', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1307, 53, 'Day 7: Konglor Cave Road Trip — Cave', 'moderate', 'Konglor Cave Road Trip (B,L)
The New tarmac road from Khoun Kham is a joy to ride the livestock and villages smile and wave and welcome us with friendly calls the limestone karst peaks loom over the valley. 
At the end of the road KongLor cave gaps wide. One of the longest water cave systems is navigated expertly by the pilots of the native longboats , there is an illuminated section so you can experience the stalagmites. The Journey through the cave is one of the highlights of Laos.
Ride: 84 KM 
Overnight in Ban Nahin', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1308, 53, 'Day 8: Ban Nahin — Bike', 'moderate', 'Ban Nahin - Lak Seo (B,L)
We follow Route 8 east to the Vietnam border there is lots to see on the way as this road is part of the famous motorbike ride the Thakhek loop. 
Lunch is served at ‘Cool Pool’ here we can swim in the crystal blue waters and take a picnic with locals. 
The bustling border town of Lak Seo is our last stop in Laos and in the morning we will leave early to cross the border into Vietnam
Ride 74KM
Overnight in Lak Seo', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1309, 53, 'Day 9: Lak Seo — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Lak Seo - Vinh (B,L)
A short Cycle  to border point 
We say goodbye to our Laos team and meet up with your new crew after crossing the border into Vietnam. From the border, we drive toward Vinh for overnight. On the way, we will stop at Kim Lien village, the birthplace of Ho Chi Minh to visit his house and a museum dedicated to him. After the visit transfer by road out of the mountains on to Vinh arriving late this afternoon. Dinner and overnight in Vinh.
Ride 30km', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1310, 53, 'Day 10: Vinh — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Vinh – Huong Khe (B,L)
Following breakfast, transfer 40 km by bus to the Ho Chi Minh highway to the town of Pho Chau, the start of today’s ride. The journey winds through lush jungle and beautiful villages nestled under the Truong Son mountain range. During the ride, take your time to admire the stunning scenery and the intricate karst formations. After a long day of pedalling, arrive in the remote town of Huong Khe. Located in Nghe An province, this small town is a quiet place to rest up for another busy day of riding. Overnight in Huong Khe.
80KM CYCLING', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1311, 53, 'Day 11: Huong Khe — Cave', 'moderate', 'Huong Khe– Phong Nha (B,L)
Continue along the Ho Chi Minh Highway today to Phong Nha. The route is still a dream to ride on and you’ll appreciate the smooth tarmac as the mountains rise and the road winds up, down and along the hillsides. The scenery is spectacular and the road is tranquil. After cycling around 80km, trade in your bike for a restful 1 hour bus journey to Phong Nha National Park. The park contains one of the most spectacular caves in Vietnam - a true natural wonder with 65 kilometres of tunnels and underground rivers. Formed approximately 250 million years ago Phong Nha was used as a hospital and ammunition depot during the war, and the entrance still shows evidence of attacks from fighter aircraft. There are also community projects underway with Flora and Fauna International and it may be possible to visit village initiatives and learn more about the forests of the national park before the end of today. 
Ride 80km
Overnight in Phong Nha.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1312, 53, 'Day 12: Phong Nha — Cave', 'moderate', 'Phong Nha – Cam Lo – Khe Sanh (B,L)
After an early morning exploration of Phong Nha Cave, transfer 1.5 hours by road to the Ho Chi Minh Trail to resume your ride. Pedal across the DMZ (also known as the 17th Parallel) to Cam Lo. Stop en route to visit Truong Son cemetery, a memorial to the tens of thousands of North Vietnamese soldiers who were killed in the Truong Son Mountains. From there it’s only 14 kilometres further to the town of Cam Lo and here the trail heads across the country into Laos. Finish today with a short transfer to Khe Sanh, a former US marine base and site of the infamous 1968 battle of the same name.
Ride 80km
Overnight in Khe Sanh.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1313, 53, 'Day 13: Khe Sanh — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Khe Sanh – A Luoi (B,L)
Begin this morning with a visit to the Khe Sanh combat base where relics of the war are exhibited and see the airstrip. Then ride through spectacular scenery, mainly downhill, from the Laos border to the Dakrong River. Cross the river by bridge and ride along the waterway to what was considered the southern part of the Ho Chi Minh Trail. Again enjoy a traffic-free road with rolling terrain, a nice contrast to the flat plains of the previous day’s ride. 
Overnight in A Luoi.
65KM CYCLING', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1314, 53, 'Day 14: A Luoi — Bike', 'moderate', 'A Luoi – Hue (B,L,D)
Due to the bad roads south of A Luoi, today you venture off the Ho Chi Minh Trail and head across the country to Hue. The 60km ride through the middle of Vietnam is on back roads before hitting Highway 1 just a few kilometres south of Hue. Here there is the option of transferring by road or continuing by bike to the centre of Hue. 
60KM CYCLING 
Overnight in Hue.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1315, 53, 'Day 15: Hue — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Hue (B,L)
Following breakfast, enjoy a relatively easy cycle on the back roads of Hue through lush countryside on a mix of footpaths and quiet country lanes. The day begins with a visit to the Imperial Citadel where you will explore the ruins of this grand monument to the emperors. Then, ride along backstreets, following the banks of the Perfume River to Thien Mu Pagoda. Continue through the quiet roads of Hue’s countryside to visit the royal tomb of Minh Mang a former Nguyen emperor, and loop back across the river to Hue via the funerary monument to Khai Dinh. Return to central Hue early this afternoon for time at your leisure to relax or tour more on your own. 
Ride 25km 
Overnight in Hue.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1316, 53, 'Day 16: Hue — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Hue – Hoi An (B,L,D)
Today is an epic ride with two small hills to conquer before the intense 11 km climb uphill to the top of Hai Van Pass where you will be rewarded with stunning views of the coast. With a recently opened tunnel through the mountain, there is now very little traffic on this uphill road. Cruise down the pass to Lang Co beach for a swim and lunch. Then transfer the final 35 kilometres by car to Hoi An, a UNESCO World Heritage Site. The remainder of this afternoon and evening is at your leisure to explore the narrow streets and lanes of this charming town. 
Ride 90KM 
Overnight in Hoi An.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1317, 53, 'Day 17: Hoi An — Temple', 'easy', 'Hoi An - My Son – Hoi An (B,L)
The last day of the journey is an easy ride My Son, the ancient centre of Cham civilization. Transfer a bit out of town to avoid the highway before cycling along scenic country back roads, past rice paddy fields, through a eucalyptus forest and passing many picturesque villages. The meandering road eventually leads us to My Son, once Champa’s greatest city and now an impressive archaeological site. Enjoy lunch near the temples and an afternoon spent touring around the crumbling temples before transferring back to Hoi An by bus. Overnight in Hoi An.
40KM CYCLING
END OF SERVICES', 'ACTIVE', NOW());

-- ===== NORTH TO SOUTH [BIKINGCYCLING (30)] =====
