INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1326, 54, 'Day 1: Arrival In Luang Prabang — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Arrival in Luang Prabang  (D)
Meet with our team for a short sunset ride around Luang Prabang to ensure we are confident for the journey ahead and to get acclimated to life in SE Asia.  We will have a informal trip briefing and dinner at a local vocational training restaurant 
Overnight in Luang Prabang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1327, 54, 'Day 2: Slow Boat On The Mekong — Bike', 'moderate', 'Slow boat on the Mekong  (B,L)
The bikes will be put on board while you prepare yourself for a soft-starting adventure in Northern
Laos. Few people have had the opportunity to do this. The boat meanders down the Mekong
giving you plenty of time to get to know you guide , learn about Laos and the road ahead . A Laos
Style Picnic Lunch will be served on Board . Just Relax and enjoy the scenery
Overnight in Pakbeang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1328, 54, 'Day 3: Pakbeng — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Pakbeng - Oudomxay (B)
After a brief transfer by vehicle, we’ll be cycling in very rural Laos, an area inhabited by hill tribe
villagers who eke a meagre existence from the land. Along the way you will pass villages of Phu
Thai, Thai Lu, Hmong, Thai Dam, Lao and Khamu. The people are very friendly and not yet tired of
seeing tourists. We stop at weaving villages along the way, where you still see families sitting in
the shade weaving on old looms. After climbing a 300 meter pass, a long descent brings you to
Oudomxay the capital of the Oudomxay Province.
Overnight in Oudomxay', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1329, 54, 'Day 4: Oudomxay — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Oudomxay - Nong Khiew  (B,L)
After a 1 hour uphill transfer, you will start cycling at an altitude of 1300 m. Enjoy the great views and the daily life in the Hmong villages dominating this region. A long descent will bring you to
Pak Mong, where we will have lunch. From Pak Mong, you cycle over a small road into the Valley and the scenic limestone mountains that surround Nong Khiaw. We stay overnight in a resort with fine views over the mountains and the Nam Ou River.

Overnight in Nong Khiaw', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1330, 54, 'Day 5: Waterfalls Trek — Waterfall', 'challenging', '100 Waterfalls trek 
Nam Ou River Cruise, 100 Waterfall Trek.
Start the day with a peaceful boat ride on the Nam Ou River. Along the way, you''ll be able to explore a small Lao village along the river. Then we''ll hike through small streams and rice paddies to reach the base of the 100 waterfalls. 
For the following few hours, you''ll see only water and jungle and hear the sound of clear waterfall cascades. Your guide will lead you through the cascades and prepare a local-style lunch on the falls in the middle of it all. 
A small villagers’ trail on the top of the 100 waterfalls will lead us back down into the valley, offering wide views over the landscapes of the Nam Ou valley along the way. Hiking back to the village we will have more time to see the daily life.
Overnight in Nong Khiaw', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1331, 54, 'Day 6: Nong Khiew — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Nong Khiew-Luang Prabang (B)
Today start with a beautiful trip down the Nam Ou River before flatter and better roads will enable
you to complete the longer distance to Luang Prabang. Only a few minor passes have to be
climbed before you are riding along the banks of the Nam Ou River, with stunning views on huge
mountain ranges. The last stage takes you through teakwood plantations before arriving in Luang Prabang.

Overnight in Luang Prabang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1332, 54, 'Day 7: Round Trip To Kuang Si Falls — Waterfall', 'moderate', 'Round Trip to Kuang Si falls  (B,L)
Your primarily road ride to the scenic Kuang Si Waterfalls will pass through Hmong and Khamu ethnic villages. Enjoy a swim in the clear water basins of the Kuang Si Waterfalls, a must see site for anyone visiting the region, Possibly Laos biggest tourist attraction.
On the return trip we will take a trip to the Laos Buffalo Dairy, an exciting project that teaches animal husbandry and bovine welfare to the local communities. Here we can pet the rabbits, feed the pigs and get a water buffalo ‘selfie’ before then we can take lunch in the pagoda and taste the water buffalo cheeses, yogurts and ice cream
.Overnight in Luang Prabang', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1333, 54, 'Day 8: Luang Prabang — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Luang Prabang - Phoukhoun (B,L)
The mountain road out of Luang Prabang takes us up to altitudes of 1400m. Breathtaking mountains views and climbs on this great day cycling. The total journey total 120km,so we can jump in the van and transfer to the sleepy village of Phoukhoun for a nights rest in a comfy local guesthouse
Overnight in PhouKhoun', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1334, 54, 'Day 9: Transfer To Phonsavan — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Transfer to Phonsavan (B)
Up and down through small scenic valleys and over mountain ridges with stunning views. we will have a transfer to Phonsavan, where the mysterious Plains of Jars are located. 
Overnight in Phonsavan', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1335, 54, 'Day 10: Round Trip To The Plain Of Jars — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Round Trip to the Plain of Jars (B,L)
This is a perfect ride at over 1000 meters above sea level. The Plain of Jars remains a place whose mysterious past has led to diverse speculations. Why did people make these amazing stone formations and what were they used for? 
Optional day of no Cycling.
Overnight in Phonsavan', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1336, 54, 'Day 11: Phonsavan To Paksan — Bike', 'moderate', 'Phonsavan to Paksan(B,L)
After 1 hr. transfer, we''ll start cycling though very nice scenery and visit the Ancient Stupas of That Chomphet  . We have to cross some passes that will reward us with great views and travel on b roads through untouched villages.  We''ll put the bikes back on the back up car and drive the last hour to Paksang . Today ride is challenging with  long Climbs
Overnight in Paksan.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1337, 54, 'Day 12: Paksan To Konglor Cave — Cave', 'moderate', 'Paksan to Konglor Cave  (B,L)
Kong lor cave is a must see for any adventure tourist in Laos. 
Tham Kong Lo Cave, one of Southeast Asia’s unique geological wonders, is hidden deep in the Phu Hin Bun wilderness. To explore the cave, you can hire a boat from Ban Kong Lo village or you could bring your own inflatable kayak and float the 7 km through the cave.
Boats do stop throughout the 7 km cave, allowing travellers to explore a little on foot in the total darkness.
The caves, that measure a humongous 390 feet tall and over 650 feet wide, are filled with spike-like structures, subterranean gardens, fossil passages and foot-long cave pearls made from minerals.
Transfer in the morning 
Overnight in Kong Lor', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1338, 54, 'Day 13: Konglor Cave To Thakhek — Cave', 'moderate', 'Konglor Cave to Thakhek  (B)
On the road again as we travel south the cycling gets easier as we leave the mountains behind and the landscape alters. Khammouane Province and Thakhek are the hidden gems of Laos there is no better part of the country to see real Loatian people and culture, the small town of Thakhek is the epitome of laid back Laos
Overnight in Thakek', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1339, 54, 'Day 14: Thakhek To Savnnakhet — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Thakhek to Savnnakhet  (B)
Flat roads again today and more unhurried village life. Savannakhet is an important Loa Town as
Savannakhet is close to the busy Thai border. You can sense the opportunities for commerce and travel in this bustling town. It is the Second most populated town in all of Laos 
Overnight in Savnnakhet', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1340, 54, 'Day 15: Savannakhet To Salavan — Temple', 'moderate', 'Savannakhet to Salavan (B) 
Up early today to transfer to the Capital of Salavan Province to visit the UXO operations camp he we can see the continued efforts to clear the land of unexploded munitions left over from the ‘Secret War’  a  9 year US bombing campaign which dropped over 2,000,000 tonnes of explosives on Laos. We can also cycle around the ruined temple complexes before departing after lunch
This area is rich in ethnic groups, predominantly Laven.
Overnight in Salavan', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1341, 54, 'Day 16: Salavan To Paksong — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Salavan to Paksong  (B)
After Breakfast,  a beautiful flat cycle through the Bolaven plateau to the peaceful town of Paksong. The climate of the plateau with its cooler temperatures and abundant rainfall makes it the perfect place for coffee production. 
This area is rich in ethnic groups, predominantly Laven.

Overnight in Paksong', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1342, 54, 'Day 17: Paksong To Pakse — Waterfall', 'easy', 'Paksong to Pakse (B,L)
An easy ride today from Paksong to Pakse the largest southern city in Laos they is a very french fell to the town and the city is growing fast it proximity to 4000 islands and Cambodia make it the perfect stop for travellers. 
Enroute the road between Pakse and Paksong on the western edge of the plateau, visit Tad E-Tu Waterfall. Continue to Tad Fane Waterfall, the highest in Champasak Province.
Overnight in Pakse', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1343, 54, 'Day 18: Pakse — Exploration', 'easy', 'Pakse, Wat Phou and Champasak (B,D)
Today we head over the river to cycle along the mekong on the 14a, a quiet feeder road to the historical and quaint town of Champasak. Have Lunch sit with a coffee and watch the world trickle by whilst getting to know the lao-cals. 
After Lunch  we Cycle From the City centre we transfer  to the Unesco protected site of Wat Phou the oldest Khmer Hindu site outside of Cambodia this incredible ruin is one of the true hidden treasures of Laos.

Overnight in Champasak', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1344, 54, 'Day 19: Champasak — Exploration', 'moderate', 'Champasak - Don Khone (B,L)
Follow the mekong south to the mouth of the dreamy 4000 islands region here, it is recommended to find a cold beer and a hammock and watch the sunset spill into the idyllic Mekong. Welcome to pure peace and serenity of 4000 islands. 

Overnight in Don Khong', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1345, 54, 'Day 20: Don Khong To Don Khone — Waterfall', 'moderate', 'Don Khong to Don Khone (B,L)
The final morning ride through paddy fields and fertile farmland follows the river south, there are plenty of beautiful stops for snacks and photos. 
Relaxation and amazing Mekong sunsets remain at the top of the experience on this island with the added bonus of being in closer proximity to two waterfalls, a swimmable beach area, far superior food options than Don Dhet and fascinating history. It’s hard to believe that this sleepy, passive island was once the staging point for French colonial ambition.

Overnight in Don Khone', 'ACTIVE', NOW());

