INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1351, 55, 'Day 1: We Will Meet You At Your Guesthouse And Walk To Taec For A One — Temple', 'easy', 'We will meet you at your guesthouse and walk to TAEC for a one-hour video presentation at the Centre for Traditional Arts and Ethnology to gain insight into the rich and diverse cultures of Laos and the religious practices for the mountain tribes surrounding the gleaming Buddhist city. After a short presentation, we will ascend mount phousi to see the 7 sacred sites on the mountain that dominates the Luang Prabang Skyline.  The best view of the city is from The gilded stupa of Wat Chom Si high on the summit. 

We collect bikes then take the ferry across the Mekong river to the rural suburb of chomphet where we visit some of the older local  picturesque Buddhist temples before we ride to the top The Newer temples to learn about the building practices and the importance of the nature and Chi of the area and the practices and lifestyle of the monks residing in the monastery. 

We continue the tour with a short ride to Cucumber Island and meet a well known  local character, he is happy to share his skills and teach us local fishing techniques. Lunch is served local style on the sandy banks of mekong. 

Just before sunset, we will ride back to the City. Dinner will be at Khaiphaen a local NGO restaurant that provides free hospitality training to the local marginalized youth, many of whom reside in Chomphet District.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1352, 55, 'Day 2: Our Second Day Begins With A One — Trek', 'easy', 'Our second day Begins with a one-hour transfer to Phon Sa-a the beginning of the Sam Oudom Trail and we begin a 3 hour jungle trek to the remote village of Ban San Oudom a village of 80 families nestled between limestone cliffs. This serene and peaceful village is home to Hmong and Khummu communities brought together in the 1980’s to provide better sanitation and access to infrastructure. 

Village life is far removed from the city and 90% of the villagers seek a living as subsistence farmers in the mountains. After a local lunch with a local family we will meet the oldest Shamen in the village, who has been actively practicing shamamic rituals to the community of over 40 years he is happy to discuss the connection between the people, land and the spirit realm.  We can examine the tools of his trade and his role in the community.

Relax and explore this pristine natural environment before we assemble at the chief''s house for a traditional Baci ceremony, a blessing, and a Soul Cleansing given by the village and the shamen. This practice is reserved for special occasions such as births, new houses and friends or family members undertaking long journeys. Dinner is served around a traditional Pha Khao Lao table. 

After Dinner, we learn a traditional Bamboo Pole dance under the guidance of the locals 
We will stay overnight with the community in their homes.', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1353, 55, 'Day 3: Up Early In The Morning To Watch The Village Go To Work And Have A Simple Breakfast Before Meeting T — Waterfall', 'easy', 'Up early in the morning to watch the village go to work and have a simple breakfast before meeting the Truck to transfer back to the City.
Or trek 1 Day to Kuangsi Waterfall', 'ACTIVE', NOW());

