INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1382, 56, 'Day 7: Am Breakfast — Waterfall', 'challenging', '7.00 am Breakfast
8.00 am Transfer to Kuang Si Falls to see the Free the Bears sanctuary seen in the ‘Bears about the House’ BBC documentary . 
10.15 am Meet the Education Team and learn about the history and work of Free the Bears  
10.30 am Join the Education Team on a tour of the bear sanctuary.
11.15 am Help the Bear Care Team prepare enrichment toys and hide food in the bear’s forest enclosures, then watch them enjoy the fruits of your labour.
12 pm  We head back to the shop where you can purchase Free the Bears merchandise, and guests can opt to end your experience with the Education Team.
12.20  pm Lunch at the waterfalls 
1.30 pm Begin 9km trek to Long Lao Mai to stay with a Hmong Community
4.00pm Arrive in Village for Village orientation and divide into homestay dormitories 
6.30 pm Group Dinner
8.30 pm Bonfire Reflection', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1383, 56, 'Day 8: Long Lao Village Is A Busy Village With A Traditional Hmong Way Of Life — Market', 'moderate', 'Long Lao village is a busy village with a traditional Hmong way of life, which makes it a popular destination for day trips from Luang Prabang. This popularity has its drawbacks.  Many visitors come to see the traditional way of life without any understanding of the customs and traditions of the people. We would like to build a small information center to display a written code of etiquette for visitors and help tourists get more from the village experience. 
We will spend two days examining the issue and helping build the foundations for the information center. 
We depart Long Lao Mai at 4pm at return to Luang Prabang for riverside dinner and walk through the night market', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1385, 56, 'Day 10: Am Breakfast — Trek', 'challenging', '7.30 am Breakfast
8.30 am Meet the Elephant conservation center team ready to transfer to Sayabouly for the overnight elephant experience. 
ACTIVITIES INCLUDE: Travel from Luang Prabang by minivan – Boat trip – Walk Through the Forest – Picnic Lunch – Nursery Visit – Hospital Visit – Observe Elephants Bathing – Encounter Elephants & Mahouts – Dinner. 
When you arrive at Nam Tien Lake, we will transfer you to the Center by boat. Thus, you will have time to settle into your dorms. Your guide takes you to the forest. Along the way, you walk past the different enclosures where our main activities take place. After enjoying a Laotian-style picnic on a lakeside platform, you observe the bath time at the nursery, an area in the forest reserved for our youngest elephants and their mothers. When the elephants have drunk enough and returned to the woods, you will take the boat back to the Center for the hospital visit. 
Our Laotian vet assistant or biologist will introduce you to their world and tell you more about standard and uncommon injuries and their respective treatments. It is also the perfect time to ask any questions you may have about the biology of elephants. 
You will then observe one of the elephants’ daily baths and learn more about our giant guests’ playful characters. Elephants love water. 
They also use bath time to socialize and strengthen ties in the herd. After the elephants have washed, you will have the opportunity to see them up close. Their ears are flapping, tails swatting while they use the trunk and the trees for a good scratching. Meanwhile, the guide will tell you a little about the background of each elephant. 
They have all been working hard before they came here. See if you are already able to recognize the elephants while observing them. 
Now it’s time for them to walk back to the forest. After a short trek, the mahouts will decide on where the elephants can graze for the night. 
Before dinner, take a moment to take in the surroundings from on', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
INSERT INTO itineraries (id, tour_id, title, level, description, status, created_at)
VALUES (1386, 56, 'Day 11: Activities Include Breakfast — Market', 'moderate', 'ACTIVITIES INCLUDE Breakfast – Meet the elephants in the forest, observe elephants bathing, socialize area observation, and lunch. 
On the second day, you will meet up with the elephants in the forest. 
After spending the night in the jungle, it is time for another bath. Then, enjoy strolling together with these magnificent animals in their natural habitat. 
When they have had their fill of water, they are shown to the Socialization Area, this is an area where the elephants can freely interact during a big part of the day, recreating a semi-natural living environment. 
Here the elephants can enjoy being elephants. First, follow the guide around the perimeter to learn more about the group and its dynamics. Then, take your time on the different platforms to see how a new herd is being formed. This rare opportunity will bring you closer to their natural life, which is very special about our program and difficult to find anywhere else. 
Lunch is at the Center. So you have some time to relax before we bring you back to Luang Prabang by minivan. 
You can say your goodbyes to the staff at the restaurant or walk around the Center one last time. 
Return to Luang Prabang in the afternoon. 
Dinner at a local restaurant and a final stroll through the night market for Souvenirs .', 'ACTIVE', NOW());
